adviseScripts.text: Imagine there are two people,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: but only enough food for one.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: What would you do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Rock, paper, scissors.
Split the food.
Leaving it up to luck... that's not a reasonable solution.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You must choose a game of skill to determine the victor.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Boxing, for example. That would be a fine choice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: An interesting idea. I never considered it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: A respectable answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White and I talk about our favorite foods.
Scarlet is very laid back... perhaps too much so.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: It gets on my nerves on occasion.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'm considering whether to say something to her about it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Teammates should always be open with each other.
I'm sure her nonchalant attitude must have helped you out in the past.
Hm. I disagree.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Even teammates can keep secrets from each other.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: That is, so long as doing so won't cause harm to the other person.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: ... That's true.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: We once ended up avoiding a storm because Scarlet moved so slowly.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I suppose there is a positive and a negative side to everything...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White and I discuss Scarlet.
Tell me one positive thing about the Ark.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Choose only one thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: There is unlimited food.
There is a lot to do.
... What?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Unlimited?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Don't lie. There's no way something like that exists.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: A lot to do? Do you mean nightlife?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Sorry. Such things do not interest me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I introduce more aspects of the Ark to Snow White.
You all seem to eat a lot of Splendamin.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: What does it taste like? Are the portions big enough?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Does it make you feel full? Is it easy to preserve?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: The taste isn't great, but it's perfect in terms of nourishment.
I'll get you some.
... This makes me even more curious.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: If you can, get some for me at some point.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I will repay you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Thank you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I explain the different types of Splendamin to Snow White.
The human body is weak.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Yet, the mind is strong.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: How do humans keep their minds sharp?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Showers.
Sleep.
Is that true?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Then, let me use the showers here.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Sleep.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: ... It's a pity. That is something I cannot do.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I debate the true nature of the mind with Snow White.
The enemy must be killed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: No quarter must be given.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Do you agree?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I agree. They must all be crushed, no matter what.
If communication is possible, I will try talking to them first.
Easy there, tiger.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I know very well you don't actually believe that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: That's a very 'you' answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: That is the source of your strength.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White trains me in the code of conduct when encountering the enemy.
Rapunzel is quite odd.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: She'll babble on about something nonsensical, then start drooling and panting.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I don't know how I should react when that happens.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: It's best to ignore her.
Drool and pant along with her.
Scarlet said the same thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Since you both seem to think that's the best course of action, that's what I'll do.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I tried.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: She just gave me a weird look. I have no idea why...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: After all, I was just doing the same thing that she was.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Snow White tell more stories about Rapunzel.
Scarlet says crime is frequent in the Ark.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Is that true?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Absolutely not.
It's sad, but it's true.
Hm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: One of you is lying...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I just don't know who.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I don't understand.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: What would lead someone to commit a crime in such a utopia?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: It goes without saying, but there is no crime on the surface. That's because there are no humans.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White and I discuss criminology.
The Outpost is a good place.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: It's relatively safe, and has a lot of food.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: There is more than enough to live on here. Why do you still dream of reclaiming the surface?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Because this place won't be safe forever.
It's just a pipe dream.
That's true.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Nothing stays safe forever.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: A pipe dream.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: A dream that lacks the power of conviction.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I do not know how far that will carry the humans.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I tell Snow White about my hopes of one day reclaiming the surface.
Your teammates seem like good people, and your bond with them seems so strong.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Developing such a bond is no easy task.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I am curious. What is your secret?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Being handsome.
I'm not sure.
Could you please be serious?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I see. So, the bond occurs naturally?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I suppose that must be correct.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Interpersonal connections are not something that can be forced.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White and I talk about teammates.
Snow White is checking her gears.
Wait a little longer.
Speak to her.
Snow White conducted a little more maintenance.
How long have you been standing there? You didn't even say anything.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I appreciate you not interrupting me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Wait just a moment. I'll be done soon.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White conducted a little more maintenance.
Thanks for waiting.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I was finally able to finish the maintenance on my gears.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White and I have a meaningful conversation.
Do you think we'll ever reclaim the surface?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I do, because I have faith in you.
No, I don't.
You seem confident.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: ... Very well then. You can trust me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'll make it happen.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: ... I can understand where you're coming from.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: But I must reclaim the surface.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: That is the reason I exist.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White and I speak more about reclaiming the surface.
I'm not sure what your approach is with Nikkes,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: but watch yourself around any Nikkes from Inherit.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Humans are just tools to them.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'll keep that in mind.
Especially Dorothy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: But I'll stop there for now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I trust that you know how to handle yourself.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I can tell you don't trust me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I was simply giving you a friendly word of caution.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: If you'd prefer not to heed my advice, I won't force you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White and I have a conversation about Inherit.
Does the surface frighten you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Not at all.
A little bit.
I don't know if you have a lot of trust in your Nikkes, or if you're just foolhardy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Regardless, take this to heart.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Up on the surface, death is always lurking nearby.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: ... I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: And despite that fact, you still came up here?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White tells me of all the things to watch out for up on the surface.
Rapunzel once asked me if I've ever wanted
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: to go back in time and correct any mistakes I had made.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: How would you respond to this question?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I would go back in an instant.
I wouldn't go back.
So you have regrets as well...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You and I are the same.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: For me, the past should remain there.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I lost everything during the Mind Switch.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Despite that, I have no regrets, and I refuse to be lost in the past.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White and have a conversation about past regrets.
Two roads lie ahead of you. One is a road you've taken before, but it's very long.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: The other is much shorter, but unfamiliar to you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: If it was you, what road would you choose?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: The road I'm familiar with.
The new road.
You are choosing safety.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I think that is the right choice for a human being.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: As for me, I would take the other road.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: ... Unexpected.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I didn't imagine a human was capable of casting themselves into the unknown without a safety net.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'm very much the same.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: If it means I can achieve my goals more quickly, I can face any hardship.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: As I spoke with Snow White, the surface was on both of our minds.
Excluding all essential combat and survival gear,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: is there anything else you always take up to the surface?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Small snack-sized bits of Splendamin.
An Ark Ranger figurine.
Very interesting.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Would you mind letting me try some?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: And... what exactly is that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Is it something you eat?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I hand over a snack to Snow White.
Scarlet keeps trying to offer me alcohol.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: She says she feels lonely drinking alone.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: But I don't want to drink. When I'm drunk I tend to be less aware of my surroundings.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Sometimes you just need to loosen up.
Since she's lonely, you should keep her company. You can drink water.
Loosen up? In this death trap we call the surface?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: That's practically the same as committing suicide.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I will do nothing of the sort.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Oh, so that's how it is. Even if I don't drink with her, I can still be by her side.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: That was good advice. Thank you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Snow White about the surface and alcohol.
Whenever I'm on the surface, I lose all sense of time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: For me, the past, present, and future are virtually indistinguishable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: But...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'm curious,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: have you ever given the future much thought?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: We'll make a new Outpost on the surface that we can live in.
We'll be fighting tooth and nail just like we are now.
You are optimistic.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: But if that does come to pass, it would be wonderful.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: A future is indistinguishable from the present...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Yes, you are most likely correct.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I will continue fighting until the surface is once again under mankind's control.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White seems deep in thought.
If you had to choose between thunder, snow, rain or a heatwave,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: which would you prefer?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Um... Snow?
They all sound terrible.
Snow?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I remember when you were stranded and buried under the snow.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Perhaps you enjoy living life on the edge, on the brink of death?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Fine.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: These are all dangerous weather conditions for humans.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: My apologies. I did not consider this.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White and I talk about the weather.
